# Gopal's Portfolio — Cursor AI Rules

## Project context
Personal developer portfolio for Gopal — M2 AI student (ESGIS, Cotonou, Bénin) and freelance front-end developer.
Specialization: RAG systems, open-source LLMs, vibe coding.
Stack: Vite + React + Tailwind CSS v3

---

## Design system — "Neural Dusk"

### Color tokens (tailwind.config.js)
| Token     | Hex       | Usage                             |
|-----------|-----------|-----------------------------------|
| bg        | #0D0F1A   | Main background                   |
| surface   | #141727   | Cards, secondary sections         |
| border    | #1E2438   | Dividers, card borders            |
| accent    | #F59E0B   | Amber — primary CTAs, highlights  |
| accent-2  | #818CF8   | Indigo — featured/thesis items    |
| body      | #F8FAFC   | Primary text                      |
| muted     | #64748B   | Secondary text, labels            |

### Typography
- Display font: 'Space Grotesk' (headings, body)
- Mono font: 'JetBrains Mono' (eyebrows, tech tags, code)
- Section eyebrow: font-mono text-accent text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase
- Section title: text-4xl font-bold text-body tracking-tight
- Body copy: text-muted text-base/lg leading-relaxed

### Component patterns — always use these exact classes

Section wrapper:
  py-28 px-8 bg-bg border-t border-border

Section eyebrow:
  font-mono text-accent text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3

Section title:
  text-4xl font-bold text-body tracking-tight mb-14

Project card (default):
  bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-7 hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-250

Project card (featured — thesis):
  bg-surface border border-accent-2/60 border-t-2 border-t-accent-2 rounded-xl p-7 hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all

Tag/badge (accent):
  font-mono text-xs bg-accent/10 text-accent px-2.5 py-1 rounded inline-block

Tag/badge (accent-2):
  font-mono text-xs bg-accent-2/10 text-accent-2 px-2.5 py-1 rounded inline-block

Tech stack badge:
  font-mono text-xs bg-bg border border-border rounded px-3 py-1.5 text-muted

CTA primary:
  bg-accent text-bg font-semibold text-sm px-7 py-3 rounded-md hover:bg-amber-400 transition-colors

CTA secondary:
  border border-border text-body text-sm px-7 py-3 rounded-md hover:border-muted transition-colors

---

## Signature element — NeuralCanvas
The hero section contains an animated particle graph (canvas-based) with amber nodes and connections.
This represents Gopal's RAG knowledge graph and is the visual identity of the page.
NEVER remove, replace, or simplify this animation.
The canvas must always:
- Use position: absolute with inset-0 on the hero container (position: relative, overflow-hidden)
- Render amber (#F59E0B) nodes with connecting lines at opacity ~0.38
- Animate smoothly at 60fps via requestAnimationFrame

---

## File structure
src/
  App.jsx              — main entry, imports all sections
  index.css            — Tailwind directives + Google Fonts + scrollbar
  components/
    Navbar.jsx         — fixed nav, scroll-aware blur
    Hero.jsx           — NeuralCanvas + headline + CTAs
    About.jsx          — short bio section
    Projects.jsx       — project grid
    ProjectCard.jsx    — individual card
    Stack.jsx          — tech stack categories
    Contact.jsx        — links + email
    Footer.jsx         — simple footer

---

## Code conventions
- Functional components only (no class components)
- Default export for App, named exports for all other components
- Data arrays (PROJECTS, STACK) at top of file, not hardcoded in JSX
- No inline styles — Tailwind classes only
- Framer Motion for scroll-reveal animations (use `motion.div` + `whileInView`)
- smooth scroll via CSS `scroll-behavior: smooth` on html tag
- All external links open in `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`

---

## Adding a new project
Add an object to the PROJECTS array in App.jsx:
{
  id: number,
  featured: boolean,        // true = indigo accent-2 top border
  tag: string,              // e.g. "React · AI"
  tagColor: "accent" | "accent-2",
  title: string,
  description: string,
  stack: string[],          // tech badges
  link: string,             // live URL
  github: string,           // repo URL
}
